 LAUGHING"]

00:24:41.305 --> 00:24:47.574
[APPLAUSE]

00:24:47.574 --> 00:24:48.490
ROB HOTCHKISS: Thanks.

00:24:48.490 --> 00:24:50.360
So this is proof that
when you write one,

00:24:50.360 --> 00:24:51.950
you got to write two or three.

00:24:51.950 --> 00:24:57.762
So Dave mentioned I had
left Train and embarked

00:24:57.762 --> 00:24:58.470
on a solo career.

00:24:58.470 --> 00:25:00.270
The truth is I
actually disappeared

00:25:00.270 --> 00:25:02.110
for better part of a decade.

00:25:02.110 --> 00:25:03.850
And why am I doing this again?

00:25:03.850 --> 00:25:06.042
Because I wrote these songs.

00:25:06.042 --> 00:25:08.500
You write songs, are you going
to throw them in your closet

00:25:08.500 --> 00:25:10.500
or are you going to put
them in front of people?

00:25:10.500 --> 00:25:13.730
So I wrote "Blind
Faith," "Gods Laughing."

00:25:13.730 --> 00:25:15.790
"Gods Laughing," by the
way, is a pagan song.

00:25:15.790 --> 00:25:16.590
It's the gods.

00:25:16.590 --> 00:25:19.897
All those gods are
laughing, not just that one.

00:25:19.897 --> 00:25:21.980
This one's called "Glide,"
and the most recent one

00:25:21.980 --> 00:25:23.277
that I wrote.

00:25:23.277 --> 00:25:24.610
[MUSIC - ROB HOTCHKISS, "GLIDE"]

